responses.What are common flu symptoms?:
Common flu symptoms include:

- Fever
- Cough
- Headache
- Muscle aches
- Fatigue

These symptoms typically develop one to two days after being exposed to the flu virus and generally last five to seven days. However, younger, healthier individuals might experience symptoms for longer periods. Older adults or those with weakened immune systems may require additional time to recover. If you suspect you have the flu, seeking medical attention promptly can help manage its severity and ensure proper treatment.
